A man, who was brutally bashed on a train after stepping in to defend two women, speaks out about how his actions were intended to prevent any violence from erupting.

'Paul', as he has been identified, was on the train from Sydney Olympic Park to Central after the Penrith-Canterbury semi-final when he saw an argument between two women and two men.

Deciding to go over and calm things down before the situation got out of control, he came away from trying to keep the peace with a broken nose, two black eyes and 24 stitches to a gash on his head and lip. 

