Police are yet to identify the perpetrators and are continuing inquiries into the alleged assault.

They have released descriptions of the two men to the public. 

'The first is described as being of Caucasian appearance and aged 25 to 30 years. When he was last seen, the male was wearing a black shirt.

'The second man is described as being of Caucasian appearance, with a ginger beard, of a medium build, and aged in his thirties. 

'He was last seen wearing a black shirt with coloured bands around the midsection.'

Police did not confirm reports that the two men were Penrith Panthers supporters. 

Anyone with information is encouraged to contact Crimestoppers. 

